Privacy Policy for EmberAI

This Privacy Policy describes how EmberAI ("we," "our," or "the app") handles your information. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices.

1. Information We Collect

Information You Provide
• Display name, age, and gender (entered during onboarding)
• Content preference tags you select
• Custom characters you create (name, personality, backstory, images)
• Conversation messages you send to AI characters
• Custom instructions you set for individual chats

Automatically Generated Information
• A locally generated account identifier (not linked to any external account)
• Gem balance and transaction records
• Daily bonus and ad reward tracking data

2. How Your Data Is Stored

The vast majority of your data is stored entirely on your device using local storage (UserDefaults and SwiftData). This includes your profile information, conversations, custom characters, and gem balance. We do not maintain user accounts on external servers and do not require a login.

A cryptographic key is stored in your device's secure Keychain to protect the integrity of your gem balance.

3. When Data Leaves Your Device

Your data remains on your device except in the following cases:

On-Device AI (Apple Intelligence / Mochi)
When you use the on-device AI model, all processing happens locally on your iPhone. No conversation data is sent to any server.

Cloud AI Models
When you choose a cloud AI model (Llama 70B, Qwen3 32B, or Mixtral 8x7B), the messages in your current conversation are sent to our cloud API for processing. This data is used solely to generate AI responses and is not stored on our servers after the response is delivered.

Rewarded Ads
If you choose to watch rewarded ads to earn gems, the Google AdMob SDK may collect certain device and usage information in accordance with Google's privacy policy. This may include device identifiers, IP address, and ad interaction data. You can learn more at: https://policies.google.com/privacy

In-App Purchases
Gem pack purchases are processed entirely through Apple's StoreKit framework. We do not collect or have access to your payment information. Apple handles all transaction processing per their privacy policy.

4. Information We Do NOT Collect

• We do not collect your email address
• We do not require account registration or login
• We do not use analytics or crash reporting SDKs
• We do not track you across other apps or websites
• We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties
• We do not store your conversations on external servers

5. Data Retention

All conversation data and profile information is stored locally on your device. You can delete all chat history at any time from the Settings screen. Uninstalling the app removes all locally stored data.

6. Children's Privacy

EmberAI is not directed at children under the age of 17. The app collects age information during onboarding and restricts certain content to users who are 18 or older.

7. Third-Party Services

The app integrates the following third-party services:
• Apple StoreKit — for in-app purchases
• Apple FoundationModels — for on-device AI processing
• Google AdMob — for optional rewarded video ads
• Cloud AI API — for cloud-based AI model responses

Each third-party service is governed by its own privacy policy.

8. Security

We use industry-standard security measures including HMAC-SHA256 integrity verification and Apple Keychain storage to protect sensitive data on your device. Cloud API communications are transmitted over HTTPS.

9. Your Choices

• Use on-device AI only: Select the Apple on-device model to keep all conversations completely private on your device.
• Delete your data: Clear all chat history from Settings > Data > Clear All Chat History.
• Opt out of ads: Watching rewarded ads is entirely optional.
• Control content: Toggle NSFW content visibility in Settings.

10. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with an updated "Last Updated" date at the top of this page.
